# m6_p10_foundry_ramp_climb.shot — M6 P10 (2026-05-16)
#
# Regression for the "stuck at the spawn ramp / platform corner" trap on
# the foundry map. The pre-P10 spawn-ramp polygon ended at the platform's
# BOTTOM edge, leaving a 32-px vertical step at the apex that the
# multi-particle skeleton could not climb. This shot drives a Trooper
# right-walk from the foot of the LEFT ramp; after ~3 seconds of
# continuous right input he must be on top of the platform — not
# wedged at the corner.
#
# Verification:
#   - 'ramp_foot.png': mech standing at the foot of the slope
#   - 'mid_climb.png': mech mid-slope, pelvis above floor_y
#   - 'on_platform.png': mech standing on the spawn platform, pelvis
#     within ±48 px of the platform-top surface (y = 960 in foundry world
#     coords for the H=40 height)
#
# If the climb fails the contact sheet will show three near-identical
# frames stuck near the apex.

window 1280 720
seed   42 7
out    build/shots/m6_p10_foundry_ramp_climb

map foundry
loadout Trooper "Pulse Rifle" "Frag Grenades" Light Standard

# Slope foot is at (t2w(7)=224, floor_y=1152). Drop the mech a few px
# above the floor just past the foot, so the first frame already has
# him in contact with the slope.
spawn_at 240 1100
mouse    1100 600

# Press and hold RIGHT through the whole run.
at   1 press right

at  30 shot ramp_foot
at  90 shot mid_climb
at 180 shot on_platform
at 220 end

contact_sheet climb_sheet cols 3 cell 426 240
